The paper uses statistical physics notions to analyze the problem, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with heuristic analysis of the problem, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses the growth of the search tree, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also discusses the phase diagram of the 2+p-SAT model, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the resolution trajectories of the 3-SAT instances, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
